25|$|These are {{actually}} JFETs with the gate shorted to the source, and function like a two-terminal current-limiting analog to the voltage-limiting <b>Zener</b> <b>diode.</b> They allow a current through them {{to rise to}} a certain value, and then level off at a specific value. Also called CLDs, constant-current diodes, diode-connected transistors, or current-regulating diodes.|$|E
