40|$|New automatic-level-control circuit {{protects against}} signal "overshoot. " <b>Zener</b> <b>diodes</b> and series {{capacitors}} prevent voltage spikes (caused by sudden increase in input level) from appearing at output. When spike voltage drops below breakdown voltage of <b>Zener</b> <b>diodes,</b> they turn off. Initial output level {{is determined by}} Zener breakdown voltage and capacitance of series capacitor...|$|R
